start_date: In this study, we would like to ask a few questions from you to examine the types and causes of data management errors made in retracted social science papers.
We value your time so we tried to make this survey as short as possible. Completing the survey takes on average 5 minutes.
We have reached out to you via the Retraction Watch database. The study aims to flag errors potentially leading to retraction and raise awareness about the importance of clean data management.
We link your answers linked to the retracted paper only for analytical purposes.
Only your anonymised data will be publicly shared which cannot be linked to you anyhow.

This research is led byDr Balazs Aczel, ELTE University, HungaryMarton Kovacs, ELTE University, Hungary≈Ωiga Besal, University of Ljubljana, SloveniaMarton Aron Varga, ELTE University, HungaryBence Bakos, ELTE University, Hungary
The OSF page of the project: to be created
